channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden Admin Expects Iran to Attack Israel Within Days, Mulls Countermeasures
2024 Cash Dash: Harris fundraising surge more than doubles Trump's haul last month
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris hauled in $310 million in fundraising in July, more than double the $138.7 million raked in by former President Donald Trump in their 2024 election showdown

item.title: Republicans Demand Docs From Daughter of NYC Trial Judge
item.description: House Judiciary Committee Chair Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, sent a letter to the daughter of the Manhattan trial judge who presided over Donald Trump's business records case, demanding documents relating to her past work for Democrat presumptive nominee Kamala Harris.

item.title: In an Olympics of Blasphemy and Gender Controversy, Turkey's Yusuf Dike√ß is the Hero We Need
Republicans lambaste Biden for Israel weapons delays: 'Stop accommodating Iran'
item.description: Republicans in the Senate are slamming President Biden over his delay of weapons to Israel as the country continues to fight against several terrorist groups.

item.title: GARM Got Billions in Federal Contracts As They Targeted Conservatives
item.description: Four of the six largest global advertising agencies, including some who have spent much of the past decade demanding online censorship on social media platforms, have received billions of dollars from the federal government, according to a new report.

item.title: Campaign X Account Tries and Fails to Gaslight Us on Harris Word Salad for Americans Returning to US Soil
Top Dem on Trump shooting task force denies past impeachment manager role could politicize probe
item.description: Rep. Jason Crow spoke with Fox News Digital about his role as the top House Democrat on the bipartisan commission to investigate the attempted assassination of Donald Trump.

item.title: WH's Kirby: 'Nobody's Delighted' About Prisoner Swap
item.description: White House national security spokesman John Kirby said "nobody's delighted" about certain elements of the United States' prisoner swap with Russia, reported The Hill.

item.title: It's Official: Trump-Backed Former Navy SEAL Defeats Incumbent Rep. Bob Good in VA GOP Primary Recount
House Freedom Caucus chair ousted by Trump-backed challenger in Republican primary showdown
item.description: House Freedom Caucus chair Rep. Bob Good of Virginia was defeated in his bid for renomination by a rival supported by former President Trump & becomes the first House incumbent ousted by a challenger

item.title: NRA Endorses Democrat, First Time Since 2020
item.description: For the first time in four years, the National Rifle Association is endorsing a Democrat.The NRA is endorsing Rep. Mary Peltola, D-Alaska, who is running for a second term in the state's at-large district.

item.title: United States to Venezuela's Maduro: You Actually Lost the Presidential Election
House Freedom Caucus member who tried to impeach Kamala Harris wins high-profile Tennessee GOP primary
item.description: Rep. Andy Ogles faced his first re-election race on Thursday night with Tennessee's 5th Congressional District primary against a local Nashville official.

item.title: JD Vance to Newsmax: 'Call Me Weird All You Want'
item.description: Republican vice presidential nominee and sitting Sen. J.D. Vance, R-Ohio, said he'll lean into the "weird" label that's being thrown at him by the left, especially considering the source.
